	<h2>Introduction:</h2>
	This lab exercises the ability to:
	<ul>
	    <li>Perform <i>abstraction</i> by defining and calling (using) <i>user-defined <tt>function</tt>s</i> with <i>parameters</i> &amp; <i><tt>return</tt> values</i> .</li>
	</ul>
	<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

	Create Web pages which incorporate the requirements in each of the following Exercises in Reed:<br>
	Define &amp; call user-defined functions wherever possible.<br>
	Use <i>global</i> variables only for values that are constants (these constant values, specific to an application, should be defined in your user-defined library files)
	<ol>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 9.8</u> </li>
